# EC2 Instance Storage Section

## what's an EBS Volume[块] ?

* An EBS （Elastic Block Store）Volume is a network drive you can attach [连接] to your instance while they run
* It allows your instances to persist [保留] data , even after their termination [终止]
* They can only be mounted to one instance at a time (at the CCP level)
* They are bound to specific availability zone [它们绑定到特定的可用区域]
* Analogy [比喻] ：Think of them as a "network USB stick"
* Free tier [免费套餐]: 30GB of free EBS storage of type General Purpose [通用型] (SSD) or Magnetic [磁性] per month
# EBS Volume

* it's a network drive (not a physical drive)
1.  it uses the network to communicate the instance ,which means there might be a bit of latency [延迟]
2. it can be detached [分离] from an EC2 instance and attached to another one quickly
* it's locked to an Availability Zone (AZ)
1. an EBS Volume in us-east-1a can't  be attached to us-east-1b
2. to move a volume across, you first need to snapshot [快照] it.
* have a provisioned capacity [有预配置的容量] (size in GBs, and IOPS)
1. you get billed for all the provisioned capacity [需要为所有的预配置付费]
2. you can increase the capacity of the drive over time [随着时间的推移，您可以增加驱动器的容量]
## Delete on Termination attribute [终止时删除属性]

![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* controls the EBS behaviour [行为] when an EC2 instance terminates
1.  by default ,the root EBS volume is deleted (attribute enabled)
2. by default,any other attached EBS volume is not deleted (attribute disabled)
* this can be controlled by the AWS console / AWS CLI
* Use case : preserve [保留] root volume when instance is terminated
# EBS Snapshots [快照]

* make a backup [备份] (snapshot) of your EBS volume at a point in time [在某个时间点]
* not necessary to detach volume to do snapshot , but recommended [推荐]
* can copy snapshots across AZ ( availability zone )or Region [地区]
## EBS snapshots features [特征]

* EBS Snapshots Archive [归档]
1. move a snapshot to an "archive tier" [归档层] that is 75% cheaper
2. takes within [..内]24 to 72 hours for restoring the archive [24 至 72 小时内恢复存档]
* Recycle Bin [回收站] for EBS Snapshots
1. setup rules to retain [保留] deleted snapshots so you can recover them after an accidental deletion.
2. specify retention [指定保留](from 1 day to 1 year)
* Fast Snapshots Restore (FSR)
1. force full initialization of snapshot  [快照完全初始化] to have no latency on the first use (expensive $$$)
# AMI Overview

* AMI = Amazon Machine Image [映像]
* AMI are a customization [定制] of an EC2 instance
1. you add your own software, configuration, operating system, monitoring [监控] ...
2. faster boot [启动]/ configuration time because all your software is pre-packaged
* AMI are built for a specific region (and can be copied across regions)
* you can launch EC2 instances from :
1. A public AMI : AWS provided
2. your own AMI : you make and maintain [维持] them yourself
3. an aws marketplace AMI : an AMI someone else made (and potentially sells [可能出售])
## AMI Process [流程](from an EC2 instance)

* start an EC2 instance and customize it
* stop the instance (for data integrity [为了数据完整性])
* build [构建] an AMI - this will also create EBS snapshots
* launch instance from other AMIs
# EC2 Instance Store

* EBS volumes are network drives with good but "limited" performance
* if you need a high-performance [高性能] hardware disk [磁盘], use EC2 instance store
* Better I/O performance
* EC2 Instance Store lose their storage if they're stopped (ephemeral [临时存储])
* good for buffer [缓冲]/ cache / scratch [暂存数据] data / temporary content [临时内容]
* risk of data loss if hardware fails 
* backups and replication are your responsibility [备份和复制是您的责任]
>IOPS : input / output ops [ Operations] per second
# *EBS Volume Types

* EBS Volumes come in 6 types
1. gp2/gp3 (SSD) : general purposing SSD volume that balance price and performance for a wide variety of workloads [通用 SSD 卷，可平衡各种工作负载的价格和性能]
2. io1 /io 2 Block Express (SSD) : highest-performance SSD volume for mission-critical [关键任务] low-latency or high-throughput workloads [适用于关键任务低延迟或高吞吐量工作负载的最高性能 SSD 卷]
3. st1 (HDD) : Low cost HDD volume designed for frequently accessed ,throughput-intensive workloads [低成本 HDD 卷，专为频繁访问、吞吐量密集型工作负载而设计]
4. sc1(HDD) : Lowest cost HDD volume designed for less frequently accessed workloads [成本最低的 HDD 卷，专为访问频率较低的工作负载而设计]
* EBS Volumes are characterized in size | throughput | IOPS
* when in doubt always consult the AWS documention - it's good
* **only gp2/gp3 and io1 / io2 Block Express can be used as boot volumes**
